    <div class=3D"body">
        <p>One of the best known mathematical formulas is Pythagorean Theor=
em, which provides us with the relationship between the sides in a right tr=
iangle. A right triangle consists of two legs and a hypotenuse. The two leg=
s meet at a 90=C2=B0 angle and the hypotenuse is the longest side of the ri=
ght triangle and is the side opposite the right angle.</p>
<p><img width=3D"229" height=3D"190" src=3D"https://www.mathplanet.com/Olds=
ite/media/43183/triangle01.png" alt=3D"right triangle"></p>
<p>The Pythagorean Theorem tells us that the relationship in every right tr=
