<hr>
<p>There are a couple of special types of right triangles, like the 45=C2=
=B0-45=C2=B0 right triangles and the 30=C2=B0-60=C2=B0 right triangle.</p>
<p><img width=3D"445" height=3D"219" src=3D"https://www.mathplanet.com/Olds=
ite/media/43238/triangle11.png" alt=3D"right triangle"></p>
<p>Because of their angles it is easier to find the hypotenuse or the legs =
in these right triangles than in all other right triangles.</p>
<p>In a 45=C2=B0-45=C2=B0 right triangle we only need to multiply one leg b=
y =E2=88=9A2 to get the length of the hypotenuse.</p>
